---
layout: layouts/_base.njk
title: "Community Week NYC × RadicalxChange"
description: "A live conversation with NYC community builders during Community Week NYC (May 9–17, 2026)."
permalink: /communityweeknyc/index.html
introBlurb: | 
  Your voice is critical to understanding what it really means to build community: no one knows the hard work it takes behind-the-scenes better than you do. Together we are
  asking, in public and in real time, what you as community builders need to do your
  work, and what would have to change for that work to be properly
  resourced.

  The conversation is built around two questions:

  1. **What skills, resources, and infrastructure** do community builders need
     to sustain and grow their work?
  2. **What would a *community economy*** — grants, residencies, civic
     infrastructure — look like in practice?

  **Why are we doing this?**
  The bigger picture: community is civic infrastructure, and it is currently
  under-resourced, under-recognized, and under-invested in. This conversation
  is a first step toward building the evidence base for change — and we need you to be part of it.
cwnycBlurb: |
  [Community Week NYC](https://www.communityweek.nyc) is a citywide celebration of belonging that spotlights
  the organizers, spaces, and communities connecting New Yorkers. From May
  9–17, 2026, communities across all five boroughs will host events built on
  a shared belief: that being intentional about belonging builds deeper
  relationships, healthier cities, and stronger local economies. Presented by
  [Sugary NYC](https://www.sugarynyc.com/about) and [week nights](https://weeknights.co/).
rxcBlurb: |
  [RadicalxChange Foundation](/) is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization
  dedicated to democratic innovation and institutional design through
  operational partnerships and experimental projects between academia,
  government, art, technology, and beyond.
closingBlurb: |
  Join us at **"The Future of Social Connection"** on **May 15 2026**, where Jack Henderson will present a
  report-back from the engagement. The findings will feed into advocacy for better support for community builders in NYC — helping make visible the role community builders like you play, and the very real challenges you face along the way.
---

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% import "components/menu.njk" as menu %}
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% import "components/footer.njk" as footer %}
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% import "components/logo.njk" as logo %}

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% block otherHead %}
<style>
  .cwnyc-polis-embed {
    min-height: 600px;
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .cwnyc-polis-embed {
      min-height: 700px;
    }
  }
  /* pol.is/embed.js sets max-width: 0 on the injected iframe; reset it so the
     iframe fills the wrapper. Also ensure it has visible height. */
  .cwnyc-polis-embed iframe {
    width: 100% !important;
    max-width: 100% !important;
    min-height: 600px;
    border: 0;
    display: block;
  }
</style>
<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{% endblock %}

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{{ menu.render() }}

<div
  class="relative grid grid-cols-layout-4 lg:grid-cols-layout-12 py-margin lg:py-lg/margin bg-golden-fizz"
>
  <!-- Co-branded logos -->
  <header
    class="col-span-columns flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-6 gap-y-4 mb-12 lg:mb-16"
  >
    <a href="/" class="block" aria-label="RadicalxChange home">
      <img
        src="/images/logos/logo.svg"
        width="566"
        height="97"
        alt="RadicalxChange"
        class="h-12 lg:h-16 w-auto"
      />
    </a>
    <span aria-hidden="true" class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-4 leading-none"
      >×</span
    >
    <a
      href="https://www.communityweek.nyc"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="block"
      aria-label="Community Week NYC"
    >
      <!--
        TODO(cwnyc-logo): a transparent-background SVG (or PNG) is preferred
        and pending from CWNYC. The current asset is the official 1024×537
        wordmark + pigeon banner on a solid blue background — displaying
        as-is per partner direction until the transparent version arrives.
      -->
      <img
        src="/images/communityweeknyc/cwnyc-logo.png"
        width="1024"
        height="537"
        alt="Community Week NYC, May 9–17 2026"
        class="h-16 lg:h-24 w-auto"
      />
    </a>
  </header>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="col-span-columns lg:col-start-column-1 lg:col-end-gutter-9 mb-12 lg:mb-16">
    <h1 class="font-display text-size-display lg:text-size-lg/display uppercase">
      What do community builders need to thrive?
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-line-3/2 text-size-1 lg:text-size-2">
      A live conversation with NYC community builders during Community Week NYC.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section
    class="col-span-columns lg:col-start-column-1 lg:col-end-gutter-9 mb-16"
  >
    <div class="markdown">
      {{ introBlurb | markdown | safe }}
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Polis embed -->
  <section
    id="join"
    class="col-span-columns mb-16 scroll-mt-8"
  >
    <h2
      class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-4 uppercase mb-4"
    >
      Join the conversation
    </h2>
    <p class="inline-block mb-6 px-3 py-2 bg-light-gold border-2 border-black text-size--1 lg:text-size-0 font-bold uppercase tracking-wide">
      Voting closed May 14. Results below.
    </p>

    <!--
      Polis embed — Polis's documented script-based pattern
      (https://compdemocracy.org/Polis/). The script auto-creates an iframe
      pointing at https://pol.is/<conversation_id>/embed.

      The conversation_id appears in two places on this page; keep them in sync:
        1. data-conversation_id on the .polis div below
        2. the href on the "Open the conversation in a new tab" fallback link

      The inline guard below preserves a "coming soon" fallback if the ID is
      ever reverted to the POLIS_CONVO_ID_TODO sentinel — useful if the
      conversation needs to be taken offline temporarily.

      Fallback link: a direct "Open in a new tab" link is rendered beneath the
      embed in case the iframe fails to load (CSP, ad-blockers, etc.).
    -->
    <div
      class="cwnyc-polis-embed border-2 border-black bg-white relative overflow-hidden"
    >
      <div class="polis" data-conversation_id="6epckxncim"></div>
      <div
        class="cwnyc-polis-placeholder absolute inset-0 hidden flex-col items-center justify-center text-center p-8"
      >
        <p class="font-bold uppercase text-size-0 mb-2">
          Polis embed — coming soon
        </p>
        <p class="text-size--1 text-gray max-w-md">
          The live conversation will appear here once it is seeded.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <script>
      (function () {
        var slot = document.querySelector(".cwnyc-polis-embed .polis");
        if (!slot) return;
        var id = slot.getAttribute("data-conversation_id");
        if (!id || id === "POLIS_CONVO_ID_TODO") {
          slot.style.display = "none";
          var ph = document.querySelector(".cwnyc-polis-placeholder");
          if (ph) {
            ph.classList.remove("hidden");
            ph.classList.add("flex");
          }
          return;
        }
        var s = document.createElement("script");
        s.async = true;
        s.src = "https://pol.is/embed.js";
        document.head.appendChild(s);
      })();
    </script>

    <p class="mt-4 text-size--1">
      Trouble loading?
      <a
        href="https://pol.is/6epckxncim"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-link"
      >
        Open the conversation in a new tab →
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!--
    What emerged — post-conversation report, automatically populated
    from the Polis CSV exports. Do not edit by hand.

    Data source: src/site/_data/communityweekHighlights.json
    Writer: scripts/update_cwnyc_highlights.py
    Workflow: .github/workflows/update-cwnyc-highlights.yml
              (cron disabled; manual dispatch only after 2026-05-14)

    The whole section hides if `topStatements` is empty. Each inner
    subsection (consensus / divisive / groups) is independently
    gated and degrades to absence when its array is empty.

    Schema:
      {
        "lastUpdated":         "2026-05-14T20:00:00Z",
        "conversationClosed":  true,
        "stats": {
          "votes": N, "statements": N, "participants": N,
          "votersInConv": N, "commenters": N, "groups": N
        } | null,
        "topStatements": [ /* same three-card structure: label, text,
                              isUserSubmitted, votes{agree,disagree,
                              pass,total} */ ],
        "consensus": [
          { "text": "...", "isUserSubmitted": true|false,
            "votes": {...}, "minGroupAgreeRate": 0.XX }
        ],
        "divisive": [
          { "text": "...", "isUserSubmitted": true|false,
            "votes": {...},
            "groupAgreeRates": [
              { "groupId": 0, "rate": 0.XX, "n": N },
              { "groupId": 1, "rate": 0.YY, "n": N }
            ] }
        ],
        "groups": [
          { "id": 0, "size": N,
            "representativeStatements": [
              { "text": "...", "isUserSubmitted": true|false,
                "voteType": "agree"|"disagree",
                "inGroupRate": 0.XX, "outGroupRate": 0.YY,
                "inGroupN": N, "outGroupN": N, "score": 0.ZZ }
            ] }
        ]
      }
  -->
  {% if communityweekHighlights and communityweekHighlights.topStatements and communityweekHighlights.topStatements.length %}
  <section
    id="highlights"
    class="col-span-columns mb-16 scroll-mt-8"
  >
    <h2
      class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-4 uppercase mb-4"
    >
      What emerged
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-8 text-size-0 lg:text-size-1">
      Community Week NYC ran from May 8–14, with
      {% if communityweekHighlights.stats and communityweekHighlights.stats.participants %}{{ communityweekHighlights.stats.participants }}{% else %}dozens of{% endif %}
      community builders contributing to this conversation. Below is a
      summary of what emerged. The full conversation, including all
      statements and the opinion-group visualization, is
      <a class="inline-link" href="https://pol.is/6epckxncim" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">available on Polis</a>.
    </p>

    {% if communityweekHighlights.stats %}
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 border-y-2 border-black mb-12">
      <div class="py-4 lg:py-6 px-2 text-center border-r-2 border-black">
        <p class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-4 leading-none">{{ communityweekHighlights.stats.votes }}</p>
        <p class="text-size--2 lg:text-size--1 uppercase mt-2">Votes</p>
      </div>
      <div class="py-4 lg:py-6 px-2 text-center border-r-2 border-black">
        <p class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-4 leading-none">{{ communityweekHighlights.stats.statements }}</p>
        <p class="text-size--2 lg:text-size--1 uppercase mt-2">Statements</p>
      </div>
      <div class="py-4 lg:py-6 px-2 text-center">
        <p class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-4 leading-none">{{ communityweekHighlights.stats.participants }}</p>
        <p class="text-size--2 lg:text-size--1 uppercase mt-2">Participants</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    <!-- Top three at-a-glance cards -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-16">
      {% for s in communityweekHighlights.topStatements %}
      <article class="border-2 border-black p-6 flex flex-col bg-white">
        {% if s.label %}
        <p class="font-bold uppercase text-size--1 text-gray mb-3 tracking-wide">{{ s.label }}</p>
        {% endif %}
        <p class="text-size-1 lg:text-size-2 mb-6 flex-grow">“{{ s.text }}”
          {% if s.isUserSubmitted %}<span class="text-size--2 text-gray font-normal whitespace-nowrap">— submitted by a participant</span>{% endif %}
        </p>
        <div class="flex h-2 mb-2 overflow-hidden" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="block bg-black" style="width: {{ s.votes.agree }}%"></span>
          <span class="block bg-red" style="width: {{ s.votes.disagree }}%"></span>
          <span class="block bg-gray" style="width: {{ s.votes.pass }}%"></span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-size--4 text-gray">
          {{ s.votes.agree }}% agree · {{ s.votes.disagree }}% disagree · {{ s.votes.pass }}% pass · {{ s.votes.total }} votes
        </p>
      </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>

    <!-- Points of consensus -->
    {% if communityweekHighlights.consensus and communityweekHighlights.consensus.length %}
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h3 class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-2 uppercase mb-6">
        Points of consensus
      </h3>
      <ol class="space-y-6">
        {% for s in communityweekHighlights.consensus %}
        <li class="border-b border-black pb-6 last:border-b-0">
          <p class="text-size-0 lg:text-size-1 mb-3">“{{ s.text }}”
            {% if s.isUserSubmitted %}<span class="text-size--2 text-gray font-normal whitespace-nowrap">— submitted by a participant</span>{% endif %}
          </p>
          <div class="flex h-2 mb-2 overflow-hidden" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="block bg-black" style="width: {{ s.votes.agree }}%"></span>
            <span class="block bg-red" style="width: {{ s.votes.disagree }}%"></span>
            <span class="block bg-gray" style="width: {{ s.votes.pass }}%"></span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-size--4 text-gray">
            {{ s.votes.agree }}% agree · {{ s.votes.disagree }}% disagree · {{ s.votes.pass }}% pass · {{ s.votes.total }} votes
            · agreed across both opinion groups (lowest group agree rate: {{ (s.minGroupAgreeRate * 100) | round | int }}%)
          </p>
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    <!-- Where the cohort divided -->
    {% if communityweekHighlights.divisive and communityweekHighlights.divisive.length %}
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h3 class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-2 uppercase mb-6">
        Where the cohort divided
      </h3>
      <ol class="space-y-8">
        {% for s in communityweekHighlights.divisive %}
        <li class="border-b border-black pb-8 last:border-b-0">
          <p class="text-size-0 lg:text-size-1 mb-4">“{{ s.text }}”
            {% if s.isUserSubmitted %}<span class="text-size--2 text-gray font-normal whitespace-nowrap">— submitted by a participant</span>{% endif %}
          </p>
          <div class="flex h-2 mb-2 overflow-hidden" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="block bg-black" style="width: {{ s.votes.agree }}%"></span>
            <span class="block bg-red" style="width: {{ s.votes.disagree }}%"></span>
            <span class="block bg-gray" style="width: {{ s.votes.pass }}%"></span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-size--4 text-gray mb-4">
            Overall: {{ s.votes.agree }}% agree · {{ s.votes.disagree }}% disagree · {{ s.votes.pass }}% pass · {{ s.votes.total }} votes
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-2">
            {% for g in s.groupAgreeRates %}
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-1">
                <span class="text-size--2 lg:text-size--1 font-bold uppercase tracking-wide">Group {{ g.groupId + 1 }}</span>
                <span class="text-size--4 text-gray">{{ (g.rate * 100) | round | int }}% agree · n={{ g.n }}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex h-2 bg-light-gold overflow-hidden border border-black" aria-hidden="true">
                <span class="block bg-black" style="width: {{ (g.rate * 100) | round | int }}%"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    <!-- Opinion groups -->
    {% if communityweekHighlights.groups and communityweekHighlights.groups.length %}
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h3 class="font-display text-size-2 lg:text-size-2 uppercase mb-4">
        Opinion groups
      </h3>
      <p class="mb-8 text-size-0">
        Polis identified two distinct opinion groups in the conversation.
        Each is characterized below by the statements its members were
        most distinctively likely to agree or disagree with.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        {% for g in communityweekHighlights.groups %}
        <div class="border-2 border-black p-6 bg-white">
          <p class="font-bold uppercase text-size-0 mb-1 tracking-wide">Group {{ g.id + 1 }}</p>
          <p class="text-size--2 text-gray mb-6">{{ g.size }} participant{% if g.size != 1 %}s{% endif %}</p>
          <ol class="space-y-5">
            {% for s in g.representativeStatements %}
            <li>
              <p class="font-bold uppercase text-size--2 text-gray mb-2 tracking-wide">
                Most distinctively {{ s.voteType }}D with
              </p>
              <p class="text-size--1 lg:text-size-0 mb-2">“{{ s.text }}”
                {% if s.isUserSubmitted %}<span class="text-size--2 text-gray font-normal whitespace-nowrap">— submitted by a participant</span>{% endif %}
              </p>
              <p class="text-size--4 text-gray">
                {{ (s.inGroupRate * 100) | round | int }}% of this group {{ s.voteType }}d
                (n={{ s.inGroupN }}), vs {{ (s.outGroupRate * 100) | round | int }}% of others
                (n={{ s.outGroupN }})
              </p>
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ol>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    {% if communityweekHighlights.lastUpdated %}
    <p class="text-size--4 text-gray">
      Last updated: {{ communityweekHighlights.lastUpdated | readableDate }}.
      Conversation data via
      <a href="https://pol.is" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Polis</a>,
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CC BY 4.0</a>.
    </p>
    {% endif %}
  </section>
  {% endif %}

  <!-- About the partners -->
  <section
    class="col-span-columns lg:col-start-column-1 lg:col-end-margin-2 mb-16"
  >
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold uppercase mb-4 text-size-0">
          About Community Week NYC
        </h3>
        <div class="markdown markdown-sm">
          {{ cwnycBlurb | markdown | safe }}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-bold uppercase mb-4 text-size-0">
          About RadicalxChange
        </h3>
        <div class="markdown markdown-sm">
          {{ rxcBlurb | markdown | safe }}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Closing -->
  <section
    class="col-span-columns lg:col-start-column-1 lg:col-end-gutter-9 space-y-line-3/2"
  >
    <div class="markdown markdown-sm">
      {{ closingBlurb | markdown | safe }}
    </div>
    <p class="text-size--1">
      Contact:
      <a href="mailto:info@radicalxchange.org" class="inline-link"
        >info@radicalxchange.org</a
      >
      (RadicalxChange) and
      <a href="mailto:hello@communityweek.nyc" class="inline-link"
        >hello@communityweek.nyc</a
      >
      (Community Week NYC).
    </p>
    <p class="text-size--1">
      <strong>Community Week participant?</strong> RxC is offering a free online
      workshop later —
      <a href="mailto:info@radicalxchange.org" class="inline-link"
        >get in touch</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>

<!-- prettier-ignore -->
{{ footer.render() }}

<script>
  // prettier-ignore
  {% include "components/menu.js" %}
</script>
